  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston begins the letter with an explanation of the cost of a bonnet. It follows with family news, reports on the health of her mother and others, and the business affairs of Hervey E. Weston.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is written on the blank pages of a circular letter advertising the Massachusetts Anti-Slavery Fair during Christmas week, 1841. The letter is soliciting for funds, volunteers, and donations for the fair, in support of the anti-slavery cause. Caroline Weston is listed among the names sponsoring the circular letter.</subfield>
